Database lock retry improvements: Reviewed and validated SQLite database lock handling

**Analysis:**
- Verified WAL mode is enabled in production (database.py:_set_sqlite_pragma)
- Verified busy_timeout is set to 30 seconds (30000ms) in database.py
- Found that worker.py stub INSERT already retries 5 times with exponential backoff
- Found that _update_worker_status already retries 5 times with exponential backoff
- Found that agent_tracker.py has comprehensive retry logic in all methods

**Changes Made:**
1. Enhanced stub INSERT retry loop (app/orchestrator/worker.py:427-456):
   - Added explicit rollback between retries (best practice)
   - Improved logging with attempt count on debug, final warning on failure
   - Maintains 5 attempts with 0.5s exponential backoff (0.5, 1.0, 1.5, 2.0s)

2. Added comprehensive test suite (tests/test_db_lock_retry.py):
   - test_update_worker_status_retries_on_db_lock: Validates retry behavior
   - test_update_worker_status_logs_on_final_failure: Validates error logging
   - test_mark_working_retries_on_db_lock: Validates AgentTracker.mark_working retry
   - test_mark_idle_retries_on_db_lock: Validates AgentTracker.mark_idle retry
   - Database configuration tests documenting production settings
   - All 6 tests passing

**Acceptance Criteria Met:**
✓ Database lock retry logic verified across all high-frequency DB writes
✓ worker_status UPDATE has 5-attempt retry with exponential backoff
✓ worker_runs INSERT has 5-attempt retry with exponential backoff
✓ agent_tracker updates all have 5-attempt retry with exponential backoff
✓ WAL mode enabled in production (prevents "database is locked")
✓ busy_timeout set to 30 seconds for high contention tolerance
✓ All tests passing (6/6 new tests, plus existing test suite)
